.P Product Version     22.14    Cadence Design Systems, Inc. 
.fi
.TH report_area  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBreport_area\fR \-  Reports the combined standard cell area in each of the hierarchy modules and the top-level design. Also reports the cell area based on different cell types if the -detail option is specified. The command provides breakdown based on the cell type (such as
.is_* attributes)
.SH Syntax \fBreport_area\fR  [-help]   [-detail]  [-hierarchical_instance <hinst_name>]  [-include_physical]              [-min_area <area_per_module>]   [-min_count <instance_count>]  [-out_file <filename>]  [-show_leaf_cells]  [-show_msv_cells]  [-sort_by {name count area}]  [-table_style {horizontal vertical}]   [-summary | -depth <depth_of_hierarchy>]                      
.P Reports the combined standard cell area in each of the hierarchy modules and the top-level design. Also reports the cell area based on different cell types if the -detail option is specified. The command provides breakdown based on the cell type (such as
.is_* attributes). The report represents the design hierarchy, and therefore, provides better readability.
.P Note: The units used in the report depend on the units used in the library. The area for each module is calculated from all the standard cells within each module using the LEF information. 
.SH Parameters   "\fB-help\fR" Prints a brief description that includes type and default information for each  report_area  parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:  man report_area   "\fB-depth <depth_of_hierarchy>\fR" Specifies the depth of hierarchy, all levels if not specified; the top of the hierarchy (design) is 1.  Data_type: int, optional   "\fB-detail\fR" Report the area in different cell type (buffer, inverter, combinational, flop, latch, clock_gate, macro, physical).  Data_type: bool, optional  "\fB-hierarchical_instance <hinst_name>\fR" Reports the area of the leaf instances in the specified hierarchical instance. You can use the -depth option to control the analysis depth of the specified hierarchical instance.  Data_type: (hinst), optional  "\fB-include_physical\fR" Specifies to include physical cells in the area calculation and report. By default, it reports only logical cells.  Data_type: bool, optional   "\fB-min_count <instance_count>                     \fR" Specifies the min instance count per module. The generated output will report the area of hinsts with number of instances greater than the specified min_count value.  Default: 0  Data_type: float, optional  "\fB-min_area <area_per_module>                             \fR" Specifies the min area per module.  The generated output will report the area of hinsts with area greater than the specified min_area lib_units.  Default: 0  Data_type: int, optional  "\fB-out_file <filename>\fR" Specifies the name of the output file.  Data_type: string, optional  "\fB-show_leaf_cells\fR" Specifies to include the leaf cells at the design level and each hinst level. These are the instances whose parent is the hinst display.  Default: 0 (Shows the hinst children in the report)  Data_type: bool, optional  "\fB-show_msv_cells\fR" Includes multiple supply voltage cells in the report. This option works with "-table_style vertical"  "\fB-sort_by {name count area}\fR" Specifies the order of hinst names.  Default: name  Data_type: bool, optional  "\fB-table_style {horizontal vertical}\fR" Specifies whether the base report should be expanded in the vertical or horizontal direction.  Default: horizontal     Data_type: enum, optional  "\fB-summary\fR" It will print the area summary for the design. It will be equivalent as doing "-depth 0".  Data_type: bool, optional 
.SH Examples
.P The following command shows the standard cell area in different base classes.
.P report_area -detail
.P (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)
.P The following command shows the leaf cells at the hinst level.
.P report_area -show_leaf_cells
